Quote: Family GOBIESOCIDAE. Small clingfish are found inshore ... About the most appropriate word for the various species is the Maori piripiri-pohutu. Pohutu means head, and piripiri is better known in the corrupted form<i> bidibid</i>. . . Diplocrepis <i>is found under stones</i> ...
